1️⃣ Code Structure & File Organization
Keep components small & reusable. Each component should handle one responsibility.

Separate concerns:

components/ → Reusable UI components

pages/ → Page-level components

hooks/ → Custom hooks

utils/ → Helper functions

context/ → Global state management

assets/ → Images, icons, styles

styles/ → Global styles, Tailwind or CSS Modules

2️⃣ Component Guidelines
✅ Use functional components with React hooks instead of class components.
✅ Extract logic into custom hooks (hooks/useFetch.js, hooks/useAuth.js).
✅ Avoid deeply nested components, split them into separate files.
✅ Use props & state efficiently, avoid unnecessary re-renders.

3️⃣ Naming Conventions
📌 Files & folders: Use camelCase for functions, PascalCase for components (Button.jsx).
📌 State variables: Use meaningful names (isLoading ✅, x ❌).
📌 Avoid abbreviations that reduce readability (fetchUserData() ✅, fUd() ❌).

4️⃣ State Management
Local state: Use useState for simple component-level state.

Context API: Use for shared app-wide state.

Redux/Zustand (if needed): For complex state logic.

Avoid prop drilling by lifting state up or using context.

5️⃣ API & Data Handling
Use fetch or Axios for API requests (utils/api.js).

Separate API calls into a dedicated file (services/api.js).

Handle loading, error, and success states properly.

6️⃣ Animations & UI
Use Framer Motion or GSAP for animations & transitions.

Keep UI smooth & engaging and let it have excessive animations.Keep a wow factor on the main page.

Ensure responsive design with Tailwind CSS or styled-components.

7️⃣ Performance Optimization
Use lazy loading (React.lazy) for components.

Optimize images with Next-gen formats (WebP).

Use useMemo & useCallback to prevent unnecessary re-renders.

8️⃣ Code Cleanliness & Formatting
Use ESLint & Prettier for consistent formatting.

Follow DRY principle (Don’t Repeat Yourself).

Comment complex logic, but avoid over-commenting obvious code
